Uses of Package
org.eng.aisp.classifier

  • Packages that use org.eng.aisp.classifier 
    Package Description
    org.eng.aisp.classifier
    Defines a general framework for training on and classifying data streams.
    org.eng.aisp.classifier.anomaly  
    org.eng.aisp.classifier.anomaly.normal  
    org.eng.aisp.classifier.cnn  
    org.eng.aisp.classifier.dcase  
    org.eng.aisp.classifier.factory  
    org.eng.aisp.classifier.gaussianmixture
    Provides an implementation of a Gaussian Mixture Model-based classifier.
    org.eng.aisp.classifier.gmm  
    org.eng.aisp.classifier.knn
    Provides a framework for classifiers that use nearest neighbor distance metrics.
    org.eng.aisp.classifier.knn.merge
    Implements nearest neighbor algorithms that merge sub-features for training and classification.
    org.eng.aisp.classifier.mvi  
    org.eng.aisp.client
    Base package for using the REST client APIs
    org.eng.aisp.client.iotp
    A framework to communicate with an asynchronous messaging service, with implementation for the IBM IoT Platform instance.
    org.eng.aisp.storage
    Base package defining requirements for the storage system used to store user profile, sensors, data windows (e\.g\.
    org.eng.aisp.tools
    Provides a set of command line tools for training, classifying, capturing, and storing sounds.
    org.eng.aisp.util
    Various utilities specific to the sound project code base.
  • Classes in org.eng.aisp.classifier used by org.eng.aisp.classifier 
    Class and Description
    AbstractClassifier
    Based class for all classifiers.
    AbstractClassifierBuilder
    Supports implementers of IClassifierBuilder.
    AbstractFixableClassifier
    Extends the superclass to support the implementation of IFixableClassifier.
    AbstractFixableFeatureExtractingClassifier
    Provides a base set of function for implementers of IFixableClassifer that need to perform feature extraction.
    AbstractFixedFeatureExtractingClassifier
    Extends the super class to implement AbstractFixedFeatureExtractingClassifier.classify(IDataWindow).
    Accuracy
    Captures model accuracy information.
    Classification
    Captures the results of a classification produced by an IFixedClassifier.
    Classification.LabelValue 
    ConfusionMatrix
    Generates a Confusion Matrix for two lists of labels.
    ConfusionMatrix.Normalization
    Defines the way the percentages are calculated in the Percents confusion matrix via #get
    IClassifier
    Adds trainability to the IFixedClassifier.
    IClassifierBuilder
    Defines function to instantiate new classifiers.
    IClassifierFactory 
    IFeatureGramClassifier
    Extends the super class to add training on ILabeledFeatureGram instances.
    IFixableClassifier
    Defines a trainable classifier from which a IFixedClassifier can be generated.
    IFixableUpdatableClassifier
    Defines a trainable classifier from which a IFixedClassifier can be generated.
    IFixedClassifier
    A implementation that can classify a data sample, but which is not trainable.
    IFixedFeatureGramClassifier
    Abstracts out the classification of IFeatureGrams.
    IUpdatableClassifier
    Defines a trainable classifier from which a IFixedClassifier can be generated.
    ModelUtil.ClassifierPerformance 
    SegmentClassification
    Contains classifications results for a specific segment of an IDataWindow defined by a start and end time in the window.
    TrainingSetInfo
    Contains information about a set of ILabeledDataWindows.
    TrainingSetInfo.LabelInfo
    Holds information about all the values that a given label name takes.
    TrainingSetInfo.LabelValueInfo
    Holds information about a single label name/value pair.
